      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. here is the current draft of the abstract:\n\n\"This study investigates the underlying mechanisms governing cognitive thresholds in large-scale transformer models. By analyzing specific patterns of failure in reasoning tasks, we identify a clear boundary between human-like cognitive processing and purely statistical pattern matching. Our findings suggest a fundamental limitation in current architectures, offering a new framework for understanding artificial intelligence development.\"\n\ncan you make it sound even more robust? specifically, i want to make sure the methodology sounds extremely rigorous so the reviewers don't question our setup. maybe add a line about the study's scale or the depth of the data to give it more weight?",
