      "beast_baseline": "that sounds way better. definitely more the \"Nature\" vibe i was going for. \n\none thing though—since the reviewers will definitely look at the methods section right after the abstract, they're gonna ask about the cohort. i'm a bit worried that mentioning we only had 10 participants might make them dismiss the whole thing as a pilot study rather than a major finding. \n\nhow should we describe the sample size in the abstract to keep that sense of rigor and scale you just added? we need to make sure they don't get hung up on the small N.",
